                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-345-off1952 t18320906-345-crimeloc1955"></join>. On the 14th of August I was in the kitchen, and saw the prisoner leave the passage; I ran after him - I took hold of his coat, tore the flap of it off, and the candlestick fell from him; I followed him to the Edgware-road - I there stumbled and fell, but I got up, and still pursued; he was taken in my sight.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. When I came out of the kitchen, did you follow me? A. You took it from the front-room; I came up to you while you were running - I followed you into a mews, where you was taken; I never lost sight of you.</p>
